INSERT INTO `recipes` VALUES (7,5,'Alvin/Dodga''s Pads','','#C16------------------------------\n#C12Forward#C20\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\nThe obtention of theses Pads are in fact a three parts quest. It''s the NPC Alvin Odeleder (located at 1500x2500, Lush Fields) for OMNI and Dodga Demercel (he can be found at Rising Sun in Aegan .. it''s a "hidden" base atop a little mountain. The entrance is hidden behind a waterfall. It''s just south of the zoneborder from wartorn valley to Aegan (check the map)) for CLAN who will give you the Pads in exchange of the completion of a mission. Special Note for the Neutral ones, they can achieve the Omni and the Clan Quest to get two top pads...\n\n#C16------------------------------\n#C12First Part#C20\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\n#L "Pads of interest" "158000"\n<img src=rdb://31537>\n#C15or#C20\n#L "Clan Shoulderpads for the Suspicious" "158087"\n<img src=rdb://31538>\n\nGo see Alvin or Dodga, select him and tell him #L "this" "/tell <myname> rshow 8" (Click on the blue sentences to say them).\n\nFrom this point, you should have a new mission in your Mission panel. Now your job is to find all the parts needed in the completion of a #L "Suspicious looking polyhedral casing - emitting strange sounds" "155721" , according to the following recipe.\n\nAll the Ingredients can be found by killing Mechdogs at Galway Country (480,980), still most clanners get them at the junkyard in Athen shire (Trash King), Bot mountain in GTC (northwest of Tir).\n\n#C16------------------------------\n#C12Recipe #C16\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156565>\n#L "Suspicious Looking Parts of Biotechnology" "155665"\n#C15+#C20\n<img src=rdb://156562>\n#L "Scrap of Notum" "155664"\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156561>\n#L "Notum infected biotechnology" "155688"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156567>\n#L "Microscopic Pulsating Nano Crystals" "155666"\n#C15+#C20\nNotum infected biotechnology\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156558>\n#L "Nano enhanced notum infected biotechnology" "155689"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156553>\n#L "Bundle of Nano-Tubes" "155683"\n#C15+#C20\nNano enhanced notum infected biotechnology\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156559>\n#L "Notum fed nano-enhanced biotechnology" "155690"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156557>\n#L "Liquid Based Conductors" "155684"\n#C15+#C20\nNotum fed nano-enhanced biotechnology\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156560>\n#L "Notum fed nano-enhanced biotechnology with some loose ends" "155718"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156566>\n#L "Large and partly fused lump of strange tetrahedral CPU bundles" "155685"\n#C15+#C20\nNotum fed nano-enhanced biotechnology withsome loose ends\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156563>\n#L "Pulsating chunk of bio-matter - surrounding a core of weird logics" "155719"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156552>\n#L "Ancient Looking Lamp Relay" "155686"\n#C15+#C20\nPulsating chunk of bio-matter - surrounding a core of weird logics\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156554>\n#L "Erratically pulsating - lukewarm chunk of biological matter" "155720"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\n<img src=rdb://156555>\n#L "Highly plastic mother-circuit array" "155687"\n#C15+#C20\nErratically pulsating - lukewarm chunk of biological matter\n#C15=#C20\n<img src=rdb://156551>\n#L "Suspicious looking polyhedral casing - emitting strange sounds" "155721"\n#C16Skills: | n/a |#C20\n\n#C14------------------------------#C20\n\nOnce you have the #L "Suspicious looking polyhedral casing - emitting strange sounds" "155721" #C20, go back seeing Alvin/Dodga trade it to him (Remember to still have the Mission !). Finally in his great goodness, he will give you back a #L "Omni-Tek/Clan Bravery Token" "158421", #L "Omni/Clan Mission Token" "96349", #L "Alvin" "155722"/#L "Dodga" "156950"''s Card I and the most awaited #L "Pads of Interest" "158000"/#L "Clan Shoulderpads for the Suspicious" "158087".\n\n\n#C16------------------------------\n#C12Comments#C16\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\nThats the end of the first part of Alvin/Dodga''s Quest. For the second part, please proceed #L "this way" "/tell <myname> rshow 9".\n\n');
INSERT INTO `recipes` VALUES (8,1000,'Alvin/Dodga''s Pads','','#C13\nSelect Alvin/Dodga and click on the blue sentences below to say them. #C20\n\n#L "Hello" "/v Hello"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Hello there! \n#L "Have you seen any strange things?" "/v Have you seen any strange things?"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: There are many things about this place that are strange and unusual, but one gets used to it over time. \n#L "Can I help you?" "/v Can I help you?"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Appearances are not everything. Just a moment...\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel pokes your belly with a strange-sounding instrument... \nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Hmm... you seem to check out all right. 82,7% biological material, that''s good enough for me.\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Now, the real question is whether or not you can be trusted to do work for Omni-Pol.\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Well, are you? \n#L "Yes" "/v Yes"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Good. Good. I''m sorry about the bio-scan, but you cannot be too careful. Strange things are all about, and a man must keep his eyes open for anything out of the ordinary these days.\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Before I tell you more, I must stress that this information you are about to receive must not be distributed to anyone else. Are we clear on this? \n#L "Yes, we are clear" "/v Yes, we are clear"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Good. I shall hold you to this promise.\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Now, for the sensitive information. I am here to gather information about a possible new threat to the Omni-Tek rule. There are rumurs about machines, robots if you like, that seem to challenge our idea of them being but a simple concoction of nuts and bolts. At present it is a small matter, but it could escalate into something bigger and much more dangerous. One must stay vigilant! Will you stay vigilant? \n#L "I will stay vigilant" "/v I will stay vigilant" \nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: Ah! But what will you be looking for, my friend? Charging in the dark are we? Well, who can blame you; I feel like I have done little else myself for the last weeks. But you look like an enterprising spirit... who knows if you''ll have better luck than me. So you''re ready for some robot hunting, are you? Serve the good cause and all that? \n#L "I''m ready for some robot hunting !" "/v I''m ready for some robot hunting !"\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: I like your spirit!\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: I need you to go and dismantle every robot you might find outside our cities and bring with you any weird-looking components you may find. Be watchful! Things might not always be what they seem. Off you go! Come back to me when you have something you think will arouse my interest.\nAlvin Odeleder/Dodga Demercel: You still here?! Go! Off with you, try to be of some use! \n\n#L "< Back the Alvin/Dodga''s Quest" "/tell <myname> rshow 7"');
INSERT INTO `recipes` VALUES (9,5,'Alvin/Dodga''s Pads','','#C12 Foreword #C20\n    You must have the #L "Alvin''s Card I" "155722" as OMNI or the /#L "Dodga''s Card I" "156950" as CLAN, which should have been given as reward in the first part of this quest.\n    To start the second Part, give him back the Card. I will start to talk "blablabla...." (nothing really worth to note) and will give you two Items :#L "TK III Decoder" "156548" and #L "Transmission Bug" "156547".\n    Now you got to wander all around Rubi-Ka to find 8 robots, select them and use the two items on them.\n\n#C12 Second Part #C20 : #L "Pads of Will" "157999"/#L "Clan Shoulderpads for the Learned" "158086"\n    Here is the list of the Robots to visit in this particular order. Select each one and wait for the end of the mission, then use the TK III Decoder on the mob (Pick up from the inventory and RightClick on the Robot) and do the same with the Transmission Bug. this time again the mission will end. Repeat the process until the end and go back to Alvin/Dodga. #C16\n    \n    - The Trash Kings [Athen Shire 1600,940] \n    - The Trash Kings Lackey [Athen Shire 1600,940] \n    - Electro Unique [Wailing wastes 600,1900] \n    - Nuts N Bolts [Wartorn Valley 715,665] \n    - Greasy Joints [Newland 900,900] \n    - Live Metal [Greater Tir County 1700,2200] \n    - Best in Brass [Galway Shire 270,850] \n    - Metalomania [Harrys 2950,3150] \n    - Galvino [Greater Omni Forest 2050,2220] #C20\n\n    The harder part of this quest being the tagging of The Trash King because his spawn time is about 3-4 hours and he is heavily camped. Still this is much better than before, it was a 18 hours camping fest a patch ago... All the others have a spawn time of 20mins. Once all the Robots have been visited, proceed to this dear Alvin/Dodga and trade him the two items. He will then reward you with : #L "Omni-Tek/Clan Bravery Token" "158421", #L "Omni/Clan Mission Token" "96349", #L "Alvin" "156545"/#L"Dodga" "156549"''s Card II as well as a #L "First update Syringe" "158088".\n    If you apply this First update Syringe on your Pads of Interest/Clan Shoulderpads for the Learned (Shift+RightClick) it will then upgrade into a #L "Pads of Will" "157999" for OMNI and into a #L "Clan Shoulderpads for the Learned" "158086" for the CLAN.\n    You can now redo the first part to wear a Pads of Interest/Clan Shoulderpads for the Suspicious with your newly acquired Pads of Will/Clan Shoulderpads for the Learned.\n    The worst part is now awaiting you, please proceed #L "this way" "/tell <myname> rshow 10".');
INSERT INTO `recipes` VALUES (10,5,'Alvin/Dodga''s Quest','','#C16------------------------------\n#C12Forward#C20\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\nYou must have the #L "Alvin" "156545"/#L "Dodga" "156549"''s Card II, given in the second part of this Quest to start the third Part.\n\nFirst you have to trade him back the card, he will then start to talk and give you a mission.\n\nNow you got to visit again the same 8 Robots as before and , much funnier now, you got to kill them all to get their chip !! (Good luck)\n\n#C16------------------------------\n#C12Third Part#C16\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\nThere is no particular order to kill the Robots. Once you got all the parts, combine them like described below : #C16\n\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=TKL" "158225"\n#C15+#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 8 Empty Slots" "158205"\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 7 Empty Slots" "158206"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=EU" "158226"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 7 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 6 Empty Slots" "158207"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=NB" "158227"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 6 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 5 Empty Slots" "158208"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=GJ" "158228"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 5 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 4 Empty Slots" "158209"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=LM" "158229"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 4 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 3 Empty Slots" "158210"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=BIB" "158230"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 3 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 2 Empty Slots" "158222"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=MM" "158231"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 2 Empty Slots\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit Rack with 1 Empty Slot" "158223"\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n#L "Communication Processing Unit ID=GV" "158232"\n#C15+#C20\nCommunication Processing Unit Rack with 1 Empty Slot\n#C15=#C20\n#L "Complex Communication Processing Unit" "158224" #C20\n#C16------------------------------#C20\n\nOnce done, go back to Alvin/Dodga and trade him back the Complex Communication Processing Unit. he will give you : #L "Omni-Tek/Clan Bravery Token" "158421", #L "Omni/Clan Mission Token" "96349", #L "Second update Syringe" "158089".\n\nAs before, you''ll use (Shift+RightClick) the Second update Syringe on the Pads of Will/Shoulderpads for the Learned to obtain the #L "Pads of Dedication" "157998" for OMNI and the #L "Clan Shoulderpads for the Veracious" "158085" for the CLAN. You can now redo the Second part to wear a Pads of Will/Clan Shoulderpads for the Learned with your newly acquired Pads of Dedication/Clan Shoulderpads for the Veracious.\n');
